{
  "function_path": "sklearn/decomposition/_fastica.py",
  "function_name": "_fit_transform",
  "justification": "This method is the core fitting procedure for FastICA (Independent Component Analysis). It accepts a 2D array (n_samples, n_features) and a boolean flag 'compute_sources' that controls whether to materialize the source matrix or only compute the unmixing matrix. It sets instance attributes for components_ (unmixing matrix), mixing_ (pseudo-inverse), mean_, whitening_, _unmixing, and n_iter_. The method supports optional whitening preprocessing with eigendecomposition (eigh) or SVD solver, handles nonlinearity functions (logcosh, exp, cube, or custom callable), and delegates to symmetric decorrelation (_ica_par) or deflation (_ica_def) algorithms for iterative refinement of the unmixing matrix. When compute_sources=True, it returns an array of shape (n_samples, n_components) with the separated source signals; when False, it returns None."
}

